<paragraph blockId="8.[125,713,1661,1685]" box="[125,713,1661,1685]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3376">Named after its occurrence in the Drakensbergen.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[138,233,137,161]" box="[138,233,137,161]" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377">
<emphasis box="[138,233,137,161]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[138,1185,185,273]" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377">
The large extension of PII is more or less similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Halik" authorityName="Halik" box="[731,1122,185,209]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbata" subGenus="Thonia">
<emphasis box="[731,1052,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377">Hygrobates (Thonia) barbata</emphasis>
Halík
</taxonomicName>
from East Africa. However, this species has the legs modified, especially on the fourth and fifth segment. No other African 
<taxonomicName box="[460,670,249,273]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[460,581,249,273]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="3377">Hygrobates</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
has a similar large extension of PII.
</paragraph>
